<item>
            <title>[MNG-1363] Transitive dependencies with system scope and version range trying to be downloaded</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MNG-1363</link>
                <project id="12316922" key="MNG">Maven (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;    &amp;lt;dependency&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;groupId&amp;gt;java&amp;lt;/groupId&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;artifactId&amp;gt;tools&amp;lt;/artifactId&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;version&amp;gt;[1.4,1.5)&amp;lt;/version&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;systemPath&amp;gt;${java.home}/../lib/tools.jar&amp;lt;/systemPath&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;scope&amp;gt;system&amp;lt;/scope&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/dependency&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If this dependency is present maven tries to download from the repo&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;No versions are present in the repository for the artifact with a range [1.4,1.5)&lt;br/&gt;
  java:tools:null:jar&lt;/p&gt;</description>
